cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with the problem of Named Entity Recognition (NER) which is a subfield of Natural Language Processing (NLP) and falls under the category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also uses recurrent neural networks (RNNs) which are a popular machine learning technique and fall under the category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper deals with the problem of binary classification which is a common problem in Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and the problem of finding named entities is a subfield of Named Entity Recognition (cs.NE).
